.TH "fpga_region_create" 9 "fpga_region_create" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
fpga_region_create \- alloc and init a struct fpga_region
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct fpga_region *" fpga_region_create
.BI "(struct device *dev "  ","
.BI "struct fpga_manager *mgr "  ","
.BI "int (*get_bridges)(struct fpga_region *) "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
device parent
.IP "mgr" 12
manager that programs this region
.IP "get_bridges" 12
optional function to get bridges to a list
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
The caller of this function is responsible for freeing the resulting region
struct with \fBfpga_region_free\fP.  Using \fBdevm_fpga_region_create\fP instead is
recommended.
.SH "RETURN"
struct fpga_region or NULL
